==English==

===Etymology===
[''late 16th century''.] Latin ''emergere'' derived from ''e''- (a variant of ''ex''-), meaning 'out, forth' and ''mergere'' meaning 'to dip'.

===Pronunciation===
* [[w:IPA_chart_for_English|IPA]]: /i.'mɚdʒ/, [[w:SAMPA/English|SAMPA]]: /i."m@`dZ/.
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɜː(r)dʒ|-ɜː(r)dʒ]]

===Intransitive Verb===
{{en-verb|emerg|ing}}

# To come into view.
# To come out of a situation, object or a liquid.
#:''Example'': The submarine emerged from the ocean.
# To become known.

